Below is a developer-focused Microsoft Dynamics 365 study plan, designed to take you from CRM basics → customization → integrations → ALM & certification.
This is the path typically used by Dynamics 365 / Power Platform developers.

Microsoft Dynamics 365 Study Plan (Developer Track)

Target roles

Dynamics 365 Developer

Power Platform Developer

CRM Technical Consultant

Recommended certification

PL-400: Power Platform Developer Associate
(Dynamics-specific dev now lives under Power Platform)

Timeline

10–12 weeks

1.5–2 hours/day

Phase 1: Dynamics 365 Core Architecture (Week 1)
Learn

Dataverse architecture

Tables (entities), columns, relationships

Solutions (managed vs unmanaged)

Security model (roles, teams, business units)

Model-driven apps vs canvas apps

Hands-on

Create a developer environment

Build custom tables

Create a model-driven app

Package everything in a solution

Phase 2: Customization & Business Logic (Weeks 2–3)
Learn

Form & view customization

Business rules

JavaScript (client-side)

Plugins (C#)

Dataverse events pipeline

Hands-on

Add JavaScript validation to forms

Write C# plugins (pre/post operation)

Debug plugins using Plugin Registration Tool

Implement synchronous & async logic

Phase 3: Power Platform Automation (Week 4)
Learn

Power Automate flows

Dataverse triggers & actions

Custom connectors (overview)

When to use Flow vs Plugin

Hands-on

Build approval workflows

Automate email notifications

Integrate with Outlook & Teams

Phase 4: Integration & APIs (Weeks 5–6)
Learn

Dataverse Web API (OData)

OAuth & Azure AD authentication

Service principals

Virtual tables

Azure integration patterns

Hands-on

Build a .NET / Node.js app calling Dataverse API

Secure API access with Azure AD

Sync data from external systems

Use Azure Functions for async integration

Phase 5: Reporting & Data (Week 7)
Learn

Dataverse querying (FetchXML)

Advanced finds

Power BI integration

Audit & change tracking

Hands-on

Build Power BI reports

Write FetchXML queries

Enable auditing

Phase 6: Application Lifecycle Management (Week 8)
Learn

Environment strategy (Dev/Test/Prod)

Solution versioning

Managed solutions

CI/CD using Azure DevOps or GitHub Actions

Hands-on

Export/import managed solutions

Build CI/CD pipeline

Automate solution deployment

Phase 7: Advanced Dynamics Development (Weeks 9–10)
Learn

Custom APIs (Dataverse)

PCF (PowerApps Component Framework)

Performance tuning

Security optimization

Hands-on

Build a PCF control

Create a Custom API

Optimize plugin performance

Phase 8: Certification & Capstone (Weeks 11–12)
Capstone Project

Build an end-to-end Dynamics 365 extension:

Custom entities

Plugins & flows

Azure Function integration

Power BI reporting

CI/CD pipeline

Certification Prep

PL-400 exam objectives

Practice exams

Hands-on revision

Developer Tech Stack

C# / .NET (primary)

JavaScript / TypeScript

Power Automate

Azure Functions

Power BI

GitHub / Azure DevOps

Best Learning Resources

Microsoft Learn → PL-400 Learning Path

Dynamics 365 Developer Docs

Power Platform GitHub samples

XrmToolBox

Plugin Registration Tool

Weekly Developer Output Checklist

By the end you should be able to:
✔ Build custom Dynamics apps
✔ Write plugins & client scripts
✔ Integrate external systems
✔ Implement CI/CD
✔ Pass PL-400 confidently

